\begin_layout Standard
In general, for N free electrons, the total electric field generated is
 the sum of the scattered fields of all of the electrons.
 This is based on the superposition principle, in which the sum of the individua
l forces yields an equivalent total force.
 The detector 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

