 Recall that only in the forward direction will this phase difference equal
 zero.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\align center
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bar{\epsilon}_{tot}=\sum_{n=1}^{N}\bar{\epsilon}_{n}=\bar{E}_{e}e^{i\phi}\sum_{n}e^{i\delta_{n}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, the total intensity is equal to the square of this total electric
