\end_layout

\end_inset

, also known as modified or incoherent scattering is the effect in which
 scattered waves have slightly different wavelengths than their incident
 x-ray wavelengths.
 This occurs when x-rays encounter loosely bound electrons, and may be explained
 by considering the incident beam to be comprised of a stream of photons
 of energy 
\begin_inset Formula $\hbar\omega_{o}$
\end_inset

, as illustrated in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
