\begin_layout Standard
In three dimensions, the diffraction condition is satisfied and the intensity
 reaches a maximum when all three fractional factors after the 
\begin_inset Formula $|F^{2}|$
\end_inset

 term in the interference function simultaneously go to zero, that is when
 the following three conditions are met:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{Q}\cdot\bar{a}=h$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{Q}\cdot\bar{b}=k$
\end_inset

 ,
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{Q}\cdot\bar{c}=l$
\end_inset

 where
\begin_inset Formula $h,k,l$
\end_inset

 are integers 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is known as the Laue condition for diffraction.
 Note that the
\begin_inset Formula $h,k,l$
\end_inset

 indices are the same indices used in describing the planes of a crystal
 in real space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The three scalar quantities describing 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{Q}$
\end_inset

 in the Laue condition are equivalent to the following vector equation,
 which also describes the reciprocal lattice vector that points perpendicular
 to the 
\begin_inset Formula $hkl$
\end_inset

 planes in real space with a length of 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{d_{hkl}}:$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{Q}=h\bar{a}^{*}+k\bar{b}^{*}+l\bar{c}^{*}=\bar{r}_{hkl}^{*}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider the scalar equation 
\begin_inset Formula $|\bar{Q}|=|\bar{r}_{hkl}^{*}|$
\end_inset

.
 Recall that 
\begin_inset Formula $|\bar{Q}|$
\end_inset

 is equivalent to 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{2sin\theta}{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 and that 
\begin_inset Formula $|\bar{r}_{hkl}^{*}|$
\end_inset

 is equivalent to the inverse of the interplanar spacing, which leads to
 Bragg's Law:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bragg's Law: 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{2sin\theta}{\lambda}=\frac{1}{d_{hkl}}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $d_{hkl}=\frac{d}{n}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

