 The structure factor times its complex conjugate, 
\begin_inset Formula $F^{2}$
\end_inset

 , affects the relative intensity of the Bragg peak and is given by summation
 of the individual atomic scattering factors of the atoms in the unit cell
 and their respective phase factors.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F=\sum_{n=0}^{N-1}f_{n}e^{2\pi i\bar{Q}\cdot\bar{r}_{n}}
\]

