\begin_inset Formula $f_{n}=(f_{0}(\frac{sin\theta}{\lambda})+\Delta f'+i\Delta f")_{n}$
\end_inset

 in general.
 We simplify this by assuming that 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{n}=(f_{0})_{n}$
\end_inset

 for atoms at positions 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{r}_{n}$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{r}_{n}=x_{n}\bar{a}+y_{n}\bar{b}+z_{n}\bar{c}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
